race.comment: ROLL ON HIGH (3) hasn't won in a long time but she looks very well suited getting to 1600m for the first time since March of 2024. Remarkably, she hasn't stepped beyond 1400m in that time despite being by Shamus Award out of a High Chaparral mare. Her last run on Melbourne Cup day gave every indication she's crying out for more ground, settling a mile back and rattling home to finish second. This looks a very winnable race and if she's not too far off the leaders on straightening, she'll round them up. MOLLY BLOOM (2) has disappointed her past two, the run three back behind Splash Back would go close. PONDALOWIE (8) is going okay, not convinced she wants 1600m but she showed versatility last time and is suited by the draw. BLINDEDBYTHELIGHT (9) backs up from very heavy ground on Champions Day at Flemington. Back in trip off that is a huge query but she's talented. PRECIOUS CHARM (4) next best.
